  "text": "The limitations of datasets that fail to cover a wide range of ethnicities lead to bias in trained models when it comes to contexts with different nationalities. Prior work has shown that visualisation techniques can be used to identify bias in training datasets by identifying population groups where a classifier tends to fail [CITATION_1] . This paper makes the following contributions in addressing population bias in driver drowsiness training datasets:",
